# D365 F&O Forms and UI

Microsoft source: [Form styles and patterns](https://learn.microsoft.com/dynamics365/fin-ops-core/dev-itpro/user-interface/form-styles-patterns)

## Core rules

- Apply **standard form pattern** via designer — avoid Custom unless required
- Use **Operational Workspace** — not legacy Workspace
- Form **extensions** + CoC classes — never overlayer
- No monster all-in-one forms
- Captions via `@LabelId`

## Scenarios and recommendations

### New transaction entry form (header + lines)

**Recommend:** **DetailsFormTransaction** or **SimpleListDetails** from pattern catalog; apply via designer.

**Avoid:** Custom pattern with manual tabs/grids fighting responsive layout.

### New role-based dashboard / hub

**Recommend:** **Operational Workspace** with tiles, tabbed lists, form parts.

**Avoid:** Legacy **Workspace** pattern (deprecated); single form with 10+ unrelated tabs.

### Add field/control to standard form

**Recommend:** **Form extension** artifact; label reference on caption; optional CoC on datasource for behavior.

**Avoid:** Overlayer base form; hardcoded `"Customer account"` caption.

### Form-only validation (user experience)

**Recommend:** CoC on form datasource `validateWrite` **and** table validation if data can be written non-UI (entity, batch).

**Avoid:** Validation only in `control.modified()` — bypassed by integration.

### Embedded child form / part

**Recommend:** Form part pattern; keep parent form focused on one process.

**Avoid:** Monster form duplicating multiple standard forms inline.

